text: Kristýna Šustrová (born 10 November 2001) is a Czech volleyball player, playing as a Opposite. She is part of the Czech Republic women's national volleyball team. She competed at the 2019 Women's European Volleyball League, winning a gold medal, and 2019 FIVB Volleyball Women's Challenger Cup. On club level she played for VK Dukla Liberec. == References == Category:2001 births Category:Living people Category:Czech volleyball players
